{
  "stem": "4830.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Horthy, ?] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] learning what has happened to the Jews, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] said that no more.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And these 40,000 people were attempting to force him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But by that time, he regained his balance and he mobilized his own troops, approximately 5,000, very well armed, mainly officers, and sent them out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And at the same time, he sent out trucks for the Jews in factories in that part of Budapest, which was at the outskirts, since, in the other outskirts, the gendarme got the Jews and deported them.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this was mainly a defensive action that they took us to the Hungarian Army from that place, and this is how I became a member of the Hungarian Army in this paramilitary unit at age 16.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because this was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] under normal circumstances, it's only age 18 they took the people in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What was the name of this paramilitary organization?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Hungarian name was [HUNGARIAN], which I-- if I translate into English, it was Labor Service.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were military units in the sense that they were belonging to the Hungarian Army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got the same ration as the members of the army, and we got even a small salary that went to those people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we got cigarettes, which we did not use at the time, and the same rations as the others.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The name of this unit-- they had the ordinary names that the Army labeled their units, and I was in the Unit 101 per 605.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there until I left this unit in October, 1944.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Budapest.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In my own home.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
